{
  "doc_id": "26534",
  "text": "At CA3-CA1 synapses, presynaptic release is modulated by retrograde effects of endocannabinoids (eCBs) in an activity-dependent way: eCBs are produced and released from CA1 dendrites using LTP-inducing paradigms (100 Hz tetanus or theta burst), and are also critical for induction of both I-LTD throughout the CA1 dendritic tree [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and for LTP at excitatory CA3-CA1 synapses [CITATION_5] . LTD requires postsynaptic release of eCBs, which in turn decreases glutamate release presynaptically [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
